Merck KGaA to Make Mappus Head of Brazilian Operations, FTD Says

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-09-16T07:25:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/merck-kgaa-to-make-mappus-head-of-brazilian-operations-ftd-says.html
Merck KGaA (MRK)  will appoint Former
Baden-Wuerttemberg Minister President Stefan Mappus to head its
Brazilian operations, the  Financial Times Deutschland  reported,
citing an internal document which the company confirmed.  Mappus will assume his new role on March 1 after six months
of training, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 